BT 1 0 0 1 0 110 Tm /F1 10 Tf 15 TL (Gary Klein's Recognition-Primed Decision model, developed from fieldwork with firefighters and military) Tj T* (commanders, showed that experts under pressure do not weigh options analytically. They recognize situations) Tj T* (as familiar and simulate the first workable solution. This predicts that AI systems functioning as decision aids) Tj T* (should amplify human pattern recognition rather than replace expert judgment. Daniel Kahneman's) Tj T* -0.029286 Tw (dual-process theory \(System 1 fast inference, System 2 deliberative reasoning\) maps directly to AI architecture:) Tj T* 0 Tw (neural networks provide System-1-like pattern evaluation while search procedures provide System-2-like) Tj T* (deliberation. Decisions produced by fast inference and those produced by deliberative chains may require) Tj T* (fundamentally different governance structures.) Tj T* ET
