BT 1 0 0 1 0 65 Tm /F1 10 Tf 15 TL (The convergence point is computational rationality, synthesized by Gershman, Horvitz, and Tenenbaum) Tj T* (\(Science, 2015\): identifying decisions with highest expected utility while accounting for computational costs.) Tj T* (Thomas Icard's Resource Rationality \(2023\) formalizes this further, proposing that decision quality must trade) Tj T* (off against the costs of computation. This framework treats bounded rationality as an optimization problem) Tj T* (rather than a deficiency, and it is the intellectual foundation for GDI's confidence threshold model.) Tj T* ET
