.278431 .333333 .411765 rg
BT 1 0 0 1 0 95 Tm /F1 10 Tf 15 TL (ARAF's foundational principle states that institutions can rely on autonomous systems only to the extent that) Tj T* (decisions can be reconstructed from contemporaneous governance records. ARAF specifies that evidence) Tj T* (must be chain-complete across the entire Decision Supply Chain: data inputs, model processing, human) Tj T* (review, and execution infrastructure. The GDR is the artifact that satisfies this requirement at each link in the) Tj T* (chain. Where ARAF asks 'can you reconstruct this decision?', GDI answers 'here is the schema-validated) Tj T* (record that makes reconstruction mechanically possible.' Organizations adopting ARAF's assessment) Tj T* (framework can use GDI's GDR as the evidence artifact that demonstrates reconstructability.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
 

Q

endstream
