BT 1 0 0 1 0 80 Tm /F1 10 Tf 15 TL (The theoretical foundations trace an unbroken line from Herbert Simon's bounded rationality \(1955\) through) Tj T* (modern computational rationality. Simon established that agents cannot evaluate all alternatives due to) Tj T* (cognitive limits, time constraints, and incomplete knowledge. They satisfice rather than optimize. His distinction) Tj T* (between procedural rationality \(how decisions are made\) and substantive rationality \(whether outcomes are) Tj T* (optimal\) maps directly to the governance question: should we govern the decision process or the decision) Tj T* (outcome? GDI's answer is both, captured in a single artifact.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
