BT 1 0 0 1 0 110 Tm /F1 10 Tf 15 TL (Automation bias, the tendency to over-rely on automated recommendations, produces two documented error) Tj T* (types: omission errors \(missing events the AI did not flag\) and commission errors \(accepting incorrect AI) Tj T* (outputs even when contradictory evidence is available\). Parasuraman and Manzey's 2010 integrative review) Tj T* (found these are manifestations of the same attentional mechanisms. In clinical settings, physicians overrode) Tj T* (their own correct decisions in 6% of cases in favor of erroneous decision support advice \(Goddard, Roudsari,) Tj T* (and Wyatt, 2012\). In high-throughput environments, decision fatigue compounds the problem: when you review) Tj T* (hundreds of identical transactions and they are all correct, you stop looking carefully. Oversight becomes a) Tj T* (rubber stamp.) Tj T* ET
